org.eclipse.incquery.viewers.runtime.model

Class ViewerState

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.incquery.viewers.runtime.model.ViewerState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IViewerLabelListener, IViewerStateListener

    public class ViewerState
extends java.lang.Object
implements IViewerStateListener, IViewerLabelListener

    A Viewer state represents a stateful data model for an IncQuery Viewer. The state is capable of either returning lists of its content, and is also capable of sending state change notifications based to IViewerStateListener implementations.

    A Viewer can be initialized directly with a set of patterns and model, or a IncQueryViewerDataModel can be used to prepare and share such data between instances.

    A ViewerState needs to be cleaned up using the dispose() method to unregister all listeners.

    Author:
    Zoltan Ujhelyi, Istvan Rath, Csaba Debreceni
